1. PURPOSE
----------
This document outlines the standard operating procedures (SOPs) for
daily clinical operations at the Contoso Health System (synthetic).

2. SCOPE
--------
Applies to all clinical staff, including physicians, nurses, and
care coordinators participating in the demo environment.

3. DAILY OPERATIONS CHECKLIST
-----------------------------
  □ Morning huddle (0800) — review overnight admissions
  □ Patient rounding schedule confirmed by 0830
  □ Care coordination handoffs completed before shift change
  □ Quality metrics dashboard reviewed by department leads
  □ Incident reports filed within 4 hours of occurrence

4. DISCHARGE PROTOCOL
---------------------
  4.1 Physician completes discharge summary within 24 hours
  4.2 Care coordinator confirms follow-up appointment scheduled
  4.3 Medication reconciliation verified by pharmacy
  4.4 Patient education materials provided and documented
  4.5 Transportation arranged if needed

5. ESCALATION PROCEDURES
-------------------------
  Level 1: Charge Nurse → Nurse Manager
  Level 2: Nurse Manager → Department Director
  Level 3: Department Director → CMO / CNO

6. DOCUMENTATION STANDARDS
--------------------------
  - All clinical notes must be completed within 24 hours
  - Use approved templates in the EHR system
  - Include patient identifiers on every page (synthetic env only)

